Counting with ADI Junior Maths has been written for pupils from Year 2 up to 7
years of age.  The work leads to attainment targets 1-3 of Key Stage 1 of the
National Curriculum in Maths (see below), and is built around the exciting theme
of a fairground.  Here, children can explore the games and practise the skills
needed for their Key Stage 1 assignments in maths.

Children of average ability would expect to achieve Level 2 in an Assignment.
Those of above average ability would achieve Level 3.  The higher levels of
games are designed to extend the more able children.

The following table shows how ADI Junior Maths 6-7 relates to the National
Curriculum in Maths:

ATTAINMENT TARGET LEVELS        1       2       3
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
AT1 Using/applying maths        X       X       x
AT2 Number                      X       x       x
AT3 Algebra                     X       x       x
AT4 Shape and space             X       x       x
AT5 Handling data               X       X       X

X - aspects of the ATs which are covered by Counting with ADI Junior 6/7. 
x - aspects of the ATs which are only partially covered by Counting with
    ADI Junior 6/7.
	


A BALLOON FOR EVERYONE IN THE HOUSE (Balloons)

COunt the number of people dropping into the house, then inflate the correct
number of balloons on the right by clicking.  Click on the Thumbs-up icon and
ADI Junior will check the answer.



NUMBERS ON THE BIG WHEEL (Big wheel)

Numbers will appear around the big wheel.  When they have disappeared, clicking
on the toaster in the middle will give you a new number to place around the
wheel.  When you have the correct sequence, click on the Thumbs-up icon and ADI
Junior will check the sequence.



COUNTING BIRDS (The bird)

Count the number of birds, then type or click on the calculator to enter the
answer.  Use the eraser icon to remove mistakes.  Click on the Thumbs-up icon
and ADI Junior will check the answer.



SAILS FOR THE BOATS (Boat)

Count the number of hulls at the bottom of the screen, then click on the groups
until the total number of sails selected matches the number of hulls.  In level
2 just the number of sails will appear.  In level 3 just numbers.



COLOURING WITH THE HELP OF FIGURES (Walking stick)

Level 1:      Paint the picture using the colour that matches the number on
              the picture.
Levels 2 & 3: Paint the picture by adding up the numbers and then choosing the
              correct colour.



VISITING THE CASTLE (castle)

Count the number of people visiting the castle and the number of people leaving
it, then type in (using the keyboard or clicking on the calculator) the number
of visitors still inside the castle.  Use the eraser icon to delete any
mistakes.  Click on the Thumbs-up icon and ADI Junior will check the number of
visitors.



THE CANDLE GAME (Clock tower)

Answer six questions correctly.  Type in the answer using either the keyboard or
by clicking on the calculator.  There is a time limit, indicated by the burning
candle.  Use the eraser icon to correct any mistakes.



DART SCORES (Dart board)

Add the scores of the darts up and either type in the answer or click on the
calculator.  Use the eraser icon to correct any mistakes.  Click on the
Thumbs-up icon and have ADI Junior check the score.




HOW TO WRITE A NUMBER (Frog)

Click on the truck or trucks which have the same total as the box on the left.
Click on the Thumbs-up icon for ADI Junior to check the number of trucks.



HOUSES IN ORDER (House)

Put the house numbers in order by clicking on the number and placing it under
the house.  The smallest number should be on the left of the screen.  If you
make a mistake, click on the number again and move it.  Click on the Thumbs-up
icon and ADI Junior will check the numbers.



HOW MANY HORSES ARE THERE IN THE PRAIRIE? (Pantomime horse)

Levels 1 & 2: Click on the number at the bottom of the screen that shows the
              number of horses.
Level 3:      The horses will run past the arrow.  Count the number of horses
              then click on the correct number. 




EACH MONKEY HAS A BANANA (Monkey)

Levels 1 & 2: Click on the toaster until there are the same number of bananas
              as monkeys.
Level 3:      The monkeys will hide when you click on the toaster.

If you made a mistake, click on a banana and drop it into the rubbish bin.

Click on the Thumbs-up icon and the monkeys will get their lunch.



FIGURES IN NUMBERS AND LETTERS (Teddy bear)

Match the word to the number on the right.



COUNTING OBJECTS (Train)

Level 1:      Add up the items in the sets.
Levels 2 & 3: Complete the sum.

Enter the total using the keyboard or by clicking on the calculator.  Use the
eraser icon to remove a mistake.  Click on the Thumbs-up icon and ADI Junior
will check the total.



THE GREATEST NUMBER OF OBJECTS (Duck)

Click on the side which has most objects in it, then click on the difference.



